{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17600498","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17600498"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T12:05:13+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T12:05:13+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15621"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15621","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15621"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.52,0.19,0.15,0.11,0.04]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8312"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71150"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8312","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8312"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15621"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56621"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"7"},{"type":"tags","id":"8"},{"type":"tags","id":"23"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1184"},{"type":"tags","id":"3081"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4936"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"7004"},{"type":"tags","id":"7536"},{"type":"tags","id":"8094"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20058"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20060"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71150","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/71150"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003ELymphocytic hypophysitis is an autoimmune condition characterized by inflammation and enlargement of the pituitary gland.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best characterizes the initial clinical presentation of lymphocytic hypophysitis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Visual disturbance","Excessive sweating","Decreased thirst","Increased appetite","Hyperglycaemia"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EIn lymphocytic hypophysitis, inflammation causes the pituitary gland to enlarge, leading to compression of surrounding structures. \u003Cstrong\u003EVisual disturbance\u003C/strong\u003E occurs due to compression of the optic chiasm, which lies directly above the pituitary gland. This is often one of the earliest symptoms.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExcessive sweating\u003C/strong\u003E is not typical. \u003Cstrong\u003EDecreased thirst\u003C/strong\u003E would not occur; if there is posterior pituitary involvement diabetes insipidus may develop causing increased thirst. \u003Cstrong\u003EIncreased appetite\u003C/strong\u003E is not a feature. \u003Cstrong\u003EHyperglycaemia\u003C/strong\u003E is not typically present in the acute phase.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe condition predominantly affects women during late pregnancy or in the early postpartum period, and typically results in varying degrees of hypopituitarism rather than increased hormone production.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Lymphocytic hypophysitis typically presents with headaches and visual disturbance due to pituitary enlargement compressing the optic chiasm","Lymphocytic hypophysitis causes hypopituitarism rather than hyperpituitarism due to inflammatory destruction of the gland","The condition most commonly affects women during late pregnancy or early postpartum period"],"references":["Langlois F, Varlamov EV, Fleseriu M. Hypophysitis, the Growing Spectrum of a Rare Pituitary Disease. J Clin Endocrinol Metab. 2022;107(1):10-28. doi:10.1210/clinem/dgab672","Kim SY. Diagnosis and Treatment of Hypopituitarism. Endocrinol Metab (Seoul). 2015 Dec;30(4):443-55. doi: 10.3803/EnM.2015.30.4.443. PMID: 26790380; PMCID: PMC4722397","Beysel S, \u00c7ali\u015fkan M, Kizilg\u00fcl M, Kan S, \u00d6zbek M, \u00c7akal E. Clinical evaluation of pituitary insufficiency in adult population. Turk J Med Sci. 2020 Jun 23;50(4):917-921. doi: 10.3906/sag-1908-19. PMID: 32283895; PMCID: PMC7379402"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56621"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15621"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56621","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56621"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-17T14:54:48+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-17T14:55:38+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8312"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71150"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"4","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf6c","name":"Endocrinology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"7","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/7"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udde0","name":"Neurology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:45+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"8","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/8"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc41","name":"Ophthalmology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:45+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"typ